<title>USA: BPA offers peak, firm power for Mon, none Sat-Sun.</title>
<headline>BPA offers peak, firm power for Mon, none Sat-Sun.</headline>
<dateline>LOS ANGELES 1997-07-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Bonneville Power Administration (BPA) continued to offer 100 megawatts of peak firm power for Monday schedulings, but offered no surplus power for Saturday or Sunday delivery, the agency said Friday.</p>
<p>BPA raised Monday prices for firm power during peak demand hours by $2.00 per megawatt hour (MWh) to $19.00 for Northwest deliveries and $20.00 for California-Oregon border (COB).</p>
<p>The agency also refrained from any non-firm offers for Monday pre-scheduing.</p>
<p>((--Los Angeles bureau, +1 213 955 6761))</p>
